## Folder structure
```
.
├── public/
│   └── images/               # SVG placeholder image slots (text-only PR safe)
├── src/
│   ├── components/           # reusable UI blocks
│   ├── data/                 # editable copy/content and schema helpers
│   ├── layouts/              # page wrapper layout + lightweight animation script
│   ├── pages/                # all routes
│   └── styles/               # global design system CSS
├── astro.config.mjs
├── package.json
└── REDESIGN_NOTES.md
```

## Remote demo image system (no binary files committed)
The site now uses **remote free-use stock demo visuals** (Unsplash Source URLs) and keeps all local assets text-based.
These images are **representative demo visuals only** and must not be presented as real Hydroseed Inc. project photos.

### Remote demo visuals currently used
- Hero image: hydroseeding/grass topic
- Hydroseeding service image
- Lawn installation image
- Commercial erosion control image
- New construction lawn image
- Lawn maintenance image
- Soil prep image
- Before/after gallery images (2 before + 2 after)
- Contact/quote image

Source mapping is centralized in `src/data/images.ts`.

### Important usage warning
- Do **not** claim these stock images are actual Hydroseed Inc. work.
- Treat them as temporary demo visuals for design presentation only.

### How to replace with real client photos later
1. Add approved client photos to your preferred image host or local `/public/images/` paths.
2. Update URLs in `src/data/images.ts` to point to those real assets.
3. Keep or improve alt text to match the actual image content.
4. Keep captions transparent unless images are verified real project photos.

### Fallback if remote URLs are blocked
If remote stock URLs fail in deployment, upload and map these filenames manually:
- `hero-hydroseeding`
- `hydroseeding-service`
- `lawn-installation`
- `commercial-erosion-control`
- `new-construction-lawn`
- `lawn-maintenance`
- `soil-prep`
- `before-lawn-1`
- `after-lawn-1`
- `before-lawn-2`
- `after-lawn-2`
- `equipment-process`
- `contact-quote`

## Animation system
- Scroll reveal (`[data-reveal]`) using IntersectionObserver.
- Staggered child reveal (`data-reveal="stagger"`) for cards.
- Subtle parallax shift for hero visual groups (`[data-parallax]`).
- Sticky desktop quote prompt toggled after scroll.

No heavy animation libraries are used.

## SEO improvements included
- Unique page titles and descriptions.
- Semantic heading structure.
- Local-intent internal links between service and location pages.
- FAQ content on homepage and detail pages.
- JSON-LD support for LocalBusiness, Service, and FAQPage.
- Sitemap route (`/sitemap.xml`) and robots route (`/robots.txt`).
- Natural keyword integration (no stuffing).

## Quote form integration options (currently frontend-only)
The form is intentionally backend-free in this demo. You can connect it via:

### Netlify Forms
- Add `name="quote"` and `data-netlify="true"` on `<form>`.
- Include hidden `<input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="quote" />`.

### Formspree
- Set `action="https://formspree.io/f/{your-id}"` and `method="POST"`.

### EmailJS
- Add client-side script with EmailJS SDK and map fields to template variables.

### Resend or custom API route
- Add server endpoint (Astro API route) and send validated payload to email service.

## Install and run
> If your environment blocks npm registry access, install commands will fail until network policy is updated.

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

## Build
```bash
npm run build
npm run preview
```

## Deploy
### Vercel
1. Push repo to GitHub.
2. Import project in Vercel.
3. Build command: `npm run build`
4. Output directory: `dist`

### Replit
1. Import repo into Replit.
2. Run `npm install`.
3. Run: `npm run dev -- --host`

## Respectful outreach framing (Tobin Studio)
- Frame this as a growth-ready redesign demo, not a teardown.
- Acknowledge existing site strengths first.
- Highlight improved lead clarity, trust presentation, and local SEO structure.
- Replace placeholders with real media, approved reviews, and owner-verified details before launch.
